Eat ... Sleep ... Train ... Repeat ... Eat ... *LAG*... Sleep ... *LAG* ... Train ... *LAG* ... Repeat ... *LAG* ... *LAG* ... *LAG* ... Repeat This game has some serious issues... Stat decay is immens and frustrating. Fights don't always seem to be fair. Touch Screen problems (can be the lag). Bugs (magical teleportation when opening stat, tournament, skills, ... screens). No Google play achievements. Game has a few interesting chapters and some extremely boring chapters. Lowering score to 1 star because of the incomprehensible, silly and extremely STUPID ending. Can't believe I wasted all this time for such an anticlimax.

Besides the fact that it's glitchy and lags alot of the time... The repetitive mechanics just weigh the game  down so much that it really feels like work instead of fun.   You spend 80 percent of the time trying to just keep your stats from dropping (you lose stats daily) and the other 19 percent trying to not starve or pass out.  When you do fight...more often than not opponents with lesser stats easily defeat you.   I love the concept of this game but it ends up being alot more work than fun.

Hard to enjoy the game when all I want to do is survive and not lose strength or agility or stamina. You also get the sense that although you could try to go each route of the tech tree only 1 or 2 are ways with which you can actually win end game...which sucks.

content: Great game concept -- but many frustrating aspects. You are given 3 paths and told essentially to choose only one to focus on, but ONLY ONE is actually good. The fact that you lose usually half a bar of each stat each day gets frustrating and then you have to spend entire 'days' at the gym recovering it.  There were just quite a few intentional bad decisions that made this game less fun than it could have been, which I feel is almost worse than laziness/bugginess. Advice -- don't ALWAYS sign up for the fights, you can skips fights with no penalty, but if you choose to sign up, you HAVE to fight on the day. Especially better at the beginning to skip a few matches to build your fighter.
